The Queensland Health eHealth project was charged with the provision of access to integrated, accurate health related information enabled by technology solutions in order to support improved clinical practices and patient outcomes. EDS' role within the eHealth alliance was to provide the architecture office and develop an enterprise architecture framework for Queensland Health. My role was within the enterprise architecture team focused on the development of the enterpise architecture framework using the TOGAF Architecture Development Method (ADM) specifically within the Information and Application architecure domains. In particular this role required the following: 
Understanding of the TOGAF ADM and its application within the Queensland Health environment for the development of the enterprise architecture framework; 
Development of the to-be information and application architecture model for Queensland Health. This required an understanding of industry reference models; 
Understanding of the Health Level 7 (HL7) functional model and messaging protocol; 
Development of standard information architecture views for payload specifications, semantic relationships and DB schemas; 
Evaluation of enterprise architecture tools with a view to adopting standard tools for modelling both enterpise architecture and solution architectures; 
Development of enterprise architecture and solution architecture artefact templates. 

